				I have played both druid and necro on PvP and blue servers.<BR>
<BR>
A summary:<BR>
<BR>
1 on 1 a necro will usually beat a druid in PvP given equal level, skill, and equipment. Those are rarely equal. Outdoors a skilled druid is unkillable 1 on 1 tho. Indoors he sucks and will usually gate.<BR>
<BR>
A necro can usually solo a single mob better.<BR>
<BR>
A druid solo's far better - He is richer, only jeweller enchanters can be richer, and hence has better gear, is totally independant, can go anywhere quickly, and the ultimate - he kills 4 mobs at a time. Not too long after reaching level 34 the average druid can be 49 easily. The necro would be happy to reach 39 in the same time. Even if that even con necro kicks his butt at 34 he is going to go back and cream him at a later date because he is 8 levels higher. Unfortunately I have been finding that they are usually OOR (8 levels below) by the time I find them again :)<BR>
<BR>
If you want to be able to brag about duelling yellow players and mobs play a necro. <BR>
