	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I don't believe many classes can beat a druid in an outdoor large terrain area.  My duel strategy is simple, cowardly, but it works almost every time.  I have SOW before duel.  I start battle by simply snaring opponent and running away.  If they have a pet the pet will eventually find me, even though the player is lost.  I kill pet far away from player.  Then I use tracking to find the player, sneak up and DOT, snare again if necessary and run away.  Again they are lost.  Repeat until player is dead or close enough that you can beat them with your DDs at that point.  They never have a chance because they can never find you long enough to do any real damage.  Since the range on DOTs is generally higher than nukes you can even stay out of nuke range usually long enough to DOT and sneak away (use camo and cover of tree for those with see invis).  Call me Ninja Druid.<BR>
<BR>
The only people hard to kill this way is others with good DOTs.  For these I general kill their pet as described above and then find a nice animal to charm and send after them.  The combo of pet against the petless, tanking, and blasting usually works on these types.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
